					<head>Commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>The commentary of Japheth ben Ali ha-Levi on the Song of Songs (fragments).</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jrb">Hebrew, Judeo-Arabic</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="119v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Shir ha-shirim</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש שיר השירים</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="en">Japheth ben Ali, ha-Levi,‏ active 10th century</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="he">יפת בן עלי, הלוי </persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>The volume contains Yefet's Arabic commentary on the Songs of Songs.</p>
								<p>The manuscript is defective at the beginning, lacking chapters 1:1-2:4 and 2:6-13.</p>
								<p>The pointed Hebrew text, accompanied by an Arabic translation, is embodied.</p>
								<p>In chapters 3:9-4:4 the punctuation is added in red ink.</p>
								<p>Chapters 5:2-7:2 and 7:4 are written in red ink, with the punctuation added in black ink.</p>
							</note>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">תם תפסיר ספר שיר השירים בעזרת משפיל ומרים מפתרון הרב הגדול מר' ור' החכם המופלא משכילנו ומזהירנו ר' <name type="person" role="author">יפת אבי עלי</name> אלבצרי האל יכפיל שכרו ויקיצו לקחת שכרו יקיים על הדרת מעלתו והמשכילים יזהירו כזוהר הרקיע וג' השלום.<locus n="119v"/>
							</colophon>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex</support>
								<extent>119 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>175</height>
										<width>133</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>125</height>
										<width>95</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>119 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>16 quires, originally of 10 leaves each (except the last which has 8 leaves).</p>
									<p>First 2 quires are lost, 3-5 are imperfect.</p>
									<p>The quires are signed with Hebrew letters and Arabic words on the upper margin of the first page.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>Lacunae after folios: 12, 21, 31, 45, 48, 61, 115.<p>Partially damaged.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="14" writtenLines="14">
									<p>Visible ruling with a mastara.</p>
									<p>The Hebrew biblical text written in red ink.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="3">
							<summary>Square and semi-cursive script of the 15th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major">
								<p>
									<locus n="12r, 12v, 21r, 21v, 31r, 31v, 45r, 45v, 48r, 48v, 61r, 61v, 115r, 115v"/>are recent restorations.</p>
								<p>
									<locus from="118r" to="119v"/>are due to a different contemporary hand.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>On folio 119v there is a beginning of a question and answer on a grammatical matter in the Song of Songs.</p>
						</additions>
